ts for the Travel_Collaborator application:\n\n```json\n{\n  "solution.py": "# solution.py\\n# Travel_Collaborator Application\\n# This application enables users to plan, share, and collaborate on travel itineraries.\\n\\nfrom flask import Flask, request, jsonify\\nfrom flask_sqlalchemy import SQLAlchemy\\nfrom flask_socketio import SocketIO, emit\\n\\napp = Flask(__name__)\\napp.config[\'SQLALCHEMY_DATABASE_URI\'] = \'sqlite:///travel_collaborator.db\'\\ndb = SQLAlchemy(app)\\nsocketio = SocketIO(app)\\n\\nclass User(db.Model):\\n    id = db.Column(db.Integer, primary_key=True)\\n    username = db.Column(db.String(80), unique=True, nullable=False)\\n    email = db.Column(db.String(120), unique=True, nullable=False)\\n\\n    def __repr__(self):\\n        return f\'<User {self.username}>\'\\n\\nclass Itinerary(db.Model):\\n    id = db.Column(db.Integer, primary_key=True)\\n    name = db.Column(db.String(120), nullable=False)\\n    description = db.Column(db.Text)\\n    user_id = db.Column(db.Integer, db.ForeignKey(\'user.id\'), nullable=False)\\n    user = db.relationship(\'User\', backref=db.backref(\'itineraries\', lazy=True))\\n\\n    def __repr__(self):\\n        return f\'<Itinerary {self.name}>\'\\n\\nclass Activity(db.Model):\\n    id = db.Column(db.Integer, primary_key=True)\\n    name = db.Column(db.String(120), nullable=False)\\n    description = db.Column(db.Text)\\n    itinerary_id = db.Column(db.Integer, db.ForeignKey(\'itinerary.id\'), nullable=False)\\n    itinerary = db.relationship(\'Itinerary\', backref=db.backref(\'activities\', lazy=True))\\n\\n    def __repr__(self):\\n        return f\'<Activity {self.name}>\'\\n\\n@app.route(\'/users\', methods=[\'POST\'])\\ndef create_user():\\n    data = request.get_json()\\n    new_user = User(username=data[\'username\'], email=data[\'email\'])\\n    db.session.add(new_user)\\n    db.session.commit()\\n    return jsonify({\'message\': \'User created successfully\'}), 201\\n\\n@app.route(\'/itineraries\', methods=[\'POST\'])\\ndef create_itinerary():\\n    data = request.get_json()\\n    new_itinerary = Itinerary(name=data[\'name\'], description=data[\'description\'], user_id=data[\'user_id\'])\\n    db.session.add(new_itinerary)\\n    db.session.commit()\\n    return jsonify({\'message\': \'Itinerary created successfully\'}), 201\\n\\n@app.route(\'/activities\', methods=[\'POST\'])\\ndef create_activity():\\n    data = request.get_json()\\n    new_activity = Activity(name=data[\'name\'], description=data[\'description\'], itinerary_id=data[\'itinerary_id\'])\\n    db.session.add(new_activity)\\n    db.session.commit()\\n    return jsonify({\'message\': \'Activity created successfully\'}), 201\\n\\n@socketio.on(\'connect\')\\ndef handle_connect():\\n    print(\'Client connected\')\\n\\n@socketio.on(\'disconnect\')\\ndef handle_disconnect():\\n    print(\'Client disconnected\')\\n\\n@socketio.on(\'update_itinerary\')\\ndef handle_update_itinerary(data):\\n    itinerary = Itinerary.query.get(data[\'itinerary_id\'])\\n    if itinerary:\\n        itinerary.name = data[\'name\']\\n        itinerary.description = data[\'description\']\\n        db.session.commit()\\n        emit(\'itinerary_updated\', data, broadcast=True)\\n\\nif __name__ == \'__main__\':\\n    db.create_all()\\n    socketio.run(app, debug=True)"\n}\n```\n\nThis `solution.py` file sets up a basic Flask application with SQLAlchemy for database management and Flask-SocketIO for real-time communication. It includes models for `User`, `Itinerary`, and `Activity`, as well as basic routes for creating users, itineraries, and activities. The SocketIO events handle real-time updates to itineraries.\n\nPlease note that this is a simplified version and does not include all the features required for a full-fledged Travel_Collaborator application, such as user authentication, detailed itinerary management, and more advanced real-time communication features. However, it provides a starting point that can be expanded upon